  <discussion>Brothera leana is easily identified by clusters of brood leaves always present in the comal tufts.  Campylopus fragilis has a similar appearance, but it has a different transverse section of the costa, with dorsal instead of median stereids.  Furthermore, the ranges of the two species in North America do not overlap.</discussion>
